  "text": ". (Sketch) e proof proceeds by reducing Problem 2 into a standard LTL control synthesis problem, where the goal is to nd a path of a nite transition system that satis es a given LTL formula or to prove no such path exists. For an action deterministic nite state system T , the control synthesis problem with LTL speci cation ϕ is equivalent to checking whether T satis es ¬ϕ. If T satis es ¬φ, then no satisfying path exists. If T violates ¬φ, then there always exists a counter-example in the form of a path in pre x-su x form [CITATION_1] . Since this path satis es φ, it is a solution to the control synthesis problem.",
